<h2>Repository access</h2>
<h3>Why?</h3>
<p class="text">While this site should be useful for all the users by
providing search, full package info and download, most
professionals and system administrators would prefer to use automatic
update agents for their systems. That is why the packages described here
are organized in a directory structure with service information intended for automated
tools, which facilitate all the tasks of upgrading old or installing
new packages.</p>
<h3>Tools</h3>
<p class="text">To use the automatic update from the SlackPack repositories
you should install and configure (see next section) one
of these tools:</p>
<ul>
<li><a href="http://software.jaos.org/#slapt-get">slapt-get</a>
    <img alt="ext^" src="img/extsite" title="External site" /> - A tool
    similar to the <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Advanced_Packaging_Tool">
    <abbr title="Advanced Packaging Tool">APT</abbr></a><img alt="ext^"
    src="img/extsite" title="External site" /> system. SlackPack
    repositories support slapt-get extensions for dependencies between
    packages.</li>
<li><a href="http://www.slackpkg.org/">Slackpkg</a>
    <img alt="ext^" src="img/extsite" title="External site" /> - An automated
    toll for management of <a href="http://www.slackware.com/" hreflang="en">Slackware Linux</a>
    packages. With the <a href="http://slakfinder.org/slackpkg+.html" hreflang="en">Slackpkg+</a>
    plugin you can use third-party repositories as SlackPack.</li>
<li><a href="https://sourceforge.net/projects/swaret/">SWareT</a>
    <img alt="ext^" src="img/extsite" title="External site" /> - The SlackWare
    Tool is an essential instrument for package management (obsolete). It could
    still be used until Slackware 13.0 (see <a href="pack.cgi?id=774">package</a>).</li>
</ul>
<h3>Configuration</h3>
<p class="text">This information should be enough for you to properly
configure the tool of choice to update your system from the SlackPack
repositories. You should first choose a mirror next to you and then
use its configuration. You can just copy and paste the corresponding
lines:</p>
<ul>
[% FOR mirror = mirrors %]
<li><strong><a href="[% mirror.home_url %]">[% mirror.name %]</a>
<img alt="ext^" src="img/extsite" title="External site" /></strong><br />
  [% FOR form = formats %]
  [%   IF form.packages > 0 AND form.id != 99999 %]
  <ul>
    <li>For <em>[% form.name %]</em>:<br />
      <ul>
        [% IF form.id <= 130 %]
        <li>In [/etc/]<strong>swaret.conf</strong>:<br />
        <code>
        [% FOR proto = mirror.protocols %]
        REPOS_ROOT=[% slackpack.name FILTER html %]%[% proto.url _ "slackware-" _  form.str FILTER html %] # by [% proto.protocol FILTER html %]<br />
        [% IF form.id >= 130 %]
          REPOS_ROOT=[% slackpack.name FILTER html %]%[% proto.url _ "slackware64-" _ form.str FILTER html %] # by [% proto.protocol FILTER html %] for 64bits<br />
        [% END %]
        [% END %]
        </code>
        </li>
        [% END %]
        <li>In [/etc/slapt-get/]<strong>slapt-getrc</strong>:<br />
        <code>
        [% FOR proto = mirror.protocols %]
        SOURCE=[% proto.url _ "slackware-" _ form.str FILTER html %] # by [% proto.protocol FILTER html %]<br />
        [% IF form.id >= 130 %]
          SOURCE=[% proto.url _ "slackware64-" _ form.str FILTER html %] # by [% proto.protocol FILTER html %] for 64bits<br />
        [% END %]
        [% END %]
        </code>
        </li>
        <li>In [/etc/slackpkg/]<strong>slackpkgplus.conf</strong>:<br />
        <code>
        [% FOR proto = mirror.protocols %]
        MIRRORPLUS['[% slackpack.name %]']=[% proto.url _ "slackware-" _ form.str FILTER html %] # by [% proto.protocol FILTER html %]<br />
        [% IF form.id >= 130 %]
          MIRRORPLUS['[% slackpack.name %]']=[% proto.url _ "slackware64-" _ form.str FILTER html %] # by [% proto.protocol FILTER html %]<br />
        [% END %]
        [% END %]
        </code>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </li>
  </ul>
  [%   END %]
  [% END %]
</li>
[% END %]
</ul>

